From: =?UTF-8?q?Petr=20P=C3=ADsa=C5=99?= <ppisar@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 20 Feb 2018 17:19:58 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Fix compiler warnings
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Most important was:

usb.c:79:50: warning: '%s' directive output may be truncated writing up to 4096 bytes into a region of size 32 [-Wformat-truncation=]
        snprintf(bus_device, BUS_DEVICE_STRSIZE, "%s:%s", bus->dirname, dev->filename);
                                                  ^~
In file included from /usr/include/stdio.h:862,
                 from usb.c:11:
/usr/include/bits/stdio2.h:64:10: note: '__builtin___snprintf_chk' output between 2 and 8194 bytes into a destination of size 32

I fixed by checking snprintf() return value and reporint it to syslog
and skipping futher code.

Other warnings about unused variables or improperly aligned "if"
statments were fixed by removing them and reindenting the code.

Signed-off-by: Petr Písař <ppisar@redhat.com>
---
 InitCardParams.c |  5 +++--
 ifdhandler.c     | 42 +++++++++++++++++++++---------------------
 usb.c            | 33 ++++++++++++++++++---------------
 3 files changed, 42 insertions(+), 38 deletions(-)

diff --git a/InitCardParams.c b/InitCardParams.c
index c4951e5..467df1f 100644
--- a/InitCardParams.c
+++ b/InitCardParams.c
@@ -15,8 +15,10 @@
 *****************************************************************************/
 #define EPSILON 0.001
 
+#ifdef ASE_DEBUG
 static int fi[16] = { 372, 372, 558, 744, 1116, 1488, 1860, 1, 
                       1, 512, 768, 1024, 1536, 2048, 1, 1 };
+#endif
 static int di[16] = { 1, 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 1, 
                       12, 20, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1 };
 static long fs[16] = {4000000, 5000000, 6000000, 8000000, 12000000, 16000000, 20000000, 0, 
@@ -49,7 +51,7 @@ static void GetDefaultReaderParams (reader* globalData, struct card_params* para
 static int MatchReaderParams(reader* globalData, char socket, struct card_params* params, ATR* atr,
                       uchar Fi, uchar Di, uchar WI, uchar N, char protocol) {
     uchar found = 0;
-    int F, D, WWT;
+    int D, WWT;
     float cardFToD = GetFToDFactor(Fi, Di);
     float readerFToD;
     int etuFactor;
@@ -85,7 +87,6 @@ static int MatchReaderParams(reader* globalData, char socket, struct card_params
     if ((readerFToD - EPSILON) <= cardFToD) {
         found = 1;
 
-        F = fi[Fi];
         D = di[Di];
 
         params->fTod = cardFToD;
